---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../data/site';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Senior backend engineer with 9+ years across Web3, DeFi, and fintech (JPMorgan, Crypto.com, Gelato, Moralis): blockchain data pipelines, exchange and wallet systems, L1/L2 infrastructure, and agentic AI tooling on top."
>
  <h1>About</h1>

  <p>
    I'm a senior backend engineer with 9+ years across Web3, DeFi, and fintech:
    JPMorgan, Crypto.com, Gelato, and currently Moralis. My day job is
    blockchain data infrastructure. At Moralis that's multi-chain wallet and
    analytics systems on ClickHouse: a wallet-profitability engine, Bitcoin and
    Solana support, and the query and caching work that decides whether any of
    it holds up once real traffic hits it. Before that: a one-click L2 rollup
    deployment pipeline at Gelato, exchange and wallet backends, and blockchain
    infrastructure at JPMorgan and Crypto.com.
  </p>

  <p>
    On top of that work I build agentic AI tooling, some internal (a Grafana MCP
    server, code-review agents with persistent memory, an automated
    post-session reviewer) and some open source (the Claude Code plugins
    ContextSpin and RecallCheck). I keep a running habit of publishing real,
    measured experiments instead of tutorials or predictions. I'd rather post
    one number I actually observed than ten opinions about where the field is
    going.
  </p>

  <h2>Background</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>9+ years across Web3, DeFi, and fintech · based in the UAE (GMT+4)</li>
    <li>
      Currently: Senior Software Engineer @ Moralis (multi-chain wallet &amp;
      analytics infra on ClickHouse)
    </li>
    <li>Past: JPMorgan, Crypto.com, Gelato, Bake</li>
    <li>
      Core stack: TypeScript/Node.js, ClickHouse, Postgres, Redis, Kafka,
      Kubernetes, AWS/GCP
    </li>
    <li>
      Ships: L2 rollup infra, multi-chain analytics on ClickHouse,
      exchange/wallet backends; plus Claude Code plugins (ContextSpin,
      RecallCheck)
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Open to new roles</h2>
  <p>
    I'm currently open to new roles. I'm looking for my next senior or
    staff-level backend or infrastructure role, ideally one with a real
    agentic-AI component. The work I do best: event-driven systems, blockchain
    and financial data pipelines, and the production plumbing that decides
    whether a feature holds up once real traffic hits it.
    <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}?subject=Role%20enquiry`}>Email me</a> and I'll
    send my full CV, or <a href="/hitesh-goel-cv.pdf">download it here</a>.
  </p>

  <p>
    I'm also open to a small number of consulting conversations with teams
    working on similar problems: agentic tooling, evals, the parts of this that
    only break in production.
  </p>

  <p>
    I'm also collecting interest for a small, private group for people building
    seriously with AI to share real experiments, no judgment unless you ask for
    it. If that's you,
    <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}?subject=AI%20Learner%20Group`}
      >email me one thing you've tried and measured</a
    >, and what happened.
  </p>

  <p>
    Find me elsewhere: <a href={SITE.social.github}>GitHub</a> ·
    <a href={SITE.social.linkedin}>LinkedIn</a> ·
    <a href={SITE.social.x}>X</a>
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
